This paper discusses the use of variational methods for Bayesian inference in neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions applications in reinforcement learning (cs.AI) and continual learning (cs.SY), which are also relevant sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of variational methods in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural engineering (cs.NE), which are less likely but still possible sub-categories.
